name: Temporal evolution of zooplankton by Regent net in the Northwestern Mediterranean Sea,Villefranche-sur-mer, 1959-2010
description: The Observatoire of Villefranche sur Mer supports the daily sampling of zooplankton since 1966 at a timeseries station located at the entrancy of the Bay of Villefranche sur Mer. Samples were collected by a horizontal tow at 5 layers, using a Regent net. Thesampling site is locatedat the mouth of the Bay over a bathymetry of 80mand is thus open to the LigurianSea. Zooplankton abundance was counted by specialistat OOV under microscopes.
